results.name: Jordan True Flight GT
results.story: The Jordan True Flight GT is a kids' shoe featuring a leather and synthetic upper with a color scheme of Cool Grey, Vivid Pink and Wolf Grey. Its mesh tongue features the iconic Jumpman logo, as does the side panel and heel. Released in 2016, the high-top sneaker comes with a heel tab to ease taking off and putting on, while a streamlined midsole promotes cushioning. Finishing the look is a tri-colored outsole with a multidirectional pattern to help with traction.

results.name: CP3.IX 'Hyper Orange'
results.story: Chris Paul’s signature CP3.IX with Jordan Brand gets a radiant rendering that sports Hyper Orange tones throughout the tongue, sockliner and outsole, while contrasting black hues emerge on the heel and mesh underlays. Complete with lateral outriggers and an inner bootie system for increased stability, the shoe also features a Zoom Air cushioning unit.

results.name: Air Jordan 8 Retro PS 'Chrome'
results.story: The ‘Chrome’ colorway of the Air Jordan 8 Retro PS blacks out the design of the retro basketball sneaker, featuring nubuck paneling on the upper construction and a dual-strap closure system that mimics the lockdown system of the Air Raid. Streaks of Light Graphite complement the design, appearing on the midsole shank, ‘23’ branding and chenille Jumpman on the tongue.

results.name: Air Jordan 8 Retro Infant 'Chrome' Gift Pack
Air Jordan 11 Retro Low BP 'Bred'
results.story: Celebrating both the 30th anniversary of the Jordan Brand and the 20th anniversary of the AJ 11, this variation of the Air Jordan 11 was one of the most highly-anticipated releases of 2015 as it brought back the iconic ‘Bred’ colorway and introduced an all-new low-top format. Like the original, the sneaker shares a predominantly black upper in patent leather and mesh atop a white midsole and translucent outsole in True Red.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro PS 'Mulberry'
results.story: The Air Jordan 7 Retro PS ‘Mulberry’ released in December 2015. Limited to kids’ sizing, the two-tone colorway features a Mulberry nubuck base with contrasting black leather overlays. A nubuck black heel panel is accented with additional pops of Mulberry on a 23-branded heel tab and nylon pull loop. The AJ7’s signature midsole detailing is rendered in a blend of white and Fuchsia Glow.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro TD 'Mulberry'
results.story: This toddler-size Air Jordan 7 appears in the ‘Mulberry’ colorway, featuring the berry-inspired tones on the majority of the upper’s nubuck paneling, while black leather accents are applied to the overlays. The shoe also incorporates a snug inner bootie construction for support, while the pull tabs on the heel allow for easy on and off. Hits of Fuchsia Glow add color to the design.

results.name: Jordan Flight Flex TR 2 GS 'Wolf Grey'
Air Jordan 6 Retro OG BG 'Maroon' 2015
results.story: The Air Jordan 6 Retro OG BG sneaker is an iconic symbol of Michael Jordan's first championship victory in 1991. This December 2015 re-release is presented in an Off-White leather upper accented by strategic placements of Maroon Red. The high-top retains all of its essential design elements with Nike branding throughout and ventilated lateral side panels. Modern tooling includes a TPU heel pull and a clear outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 6 Retro GS 'Maroon' 2016 International Release
results.story: The Air Jordan 6 GS ‘Maroon’ 2016 International Release debuted with a colorway not seen on retail shelves since 1991. The simple two-tone design makes use of an all-leather upper finished in entirely in an understated shade of Off-White, contrasted by pops of New Maroon on the molded tongue, lace toggle and midsole. Tonal Nike Air embroidery on the heel completes the OG design.

results.name: Air Jordan 8 Retro TD 'Crib Booties Pack'
Air Jordan 6 Retro BT 'Maroon'
results.story: The Air Jordan 6 Retro BT takes design cues from Michael Jordan's prized German sports car. Originally seen in 1991, this 'Maroon' kids' sneaker revives the icon's legacy with a leather upper defined by abstract lines, perforated lateral cutouts and a contrast neoprene tongue. A Jumpman logo, striped heel strap and counter embroidery add distinction to the look.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High Premium GG 'Phantom'
results.story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High Premium GG ‘Phantom’ released in November 2015 exclusively in girls’ sizing. The high-top’s upper has a monochromatic color scheme in light tan, executed in a blend of smooth and tumbled leather. The heel is adorned with an embroidered Jumpman logo, as is the woven tag stitched atop a textile tongue. It all rests on contrasting solid white tooling.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro BT 'Nothing But Net'
Air Jordan 7 Retro PS 'Nothing But Net'
Jordan Horizon 'Wolf Grey'
results.story: The Air Jordan Horizon strips down the Air Jordan 13 template, retaining its essential elements. This 'Wolf Grey' iteration is outfitted in a one-piece textile upper with premium leather lining the asymmetrical collar, traditional lacing and minimal Jumpman branding on the tongue. The underfoot platform houses dual Zoom Air units, a carbon fiber shank for midfoot integrity and strategically placed rubber outsole pods.

results.name: Jordan DNA LX 'Black'
results.story: The Jordan DNA LX sneaker is a synthesis of heritage-inspired elements that make up the iconic brand. Forming a flexible fit, this version dons a ribbed Flyknit upper with 'Gym Red' ventilation, traditional lacing threaded through TPU eyestays and a synthetic-leather counter. A Jumpman counter logo denotes the signature line's distinguished legacy. Midsole foam and sculpted rubber outsole tread structure the platform.

results.name: Air Jordan CP3.IX 'Yellow Dragon'
results.story: The Air Jordan CP3.IX 'Yellow Dragon' was released in 2015 as the ninth iteration of Chris Paul's signature shoe. The yellow and black colorway is meant to connect CP3's on-court agility with the dragon dance that's used to celebrate Chinese New Year, with black dragon scales and a partially obscured dragon insignia found on the heel. The nine-chamber Air system in the fore foot creates dynamic push-off, and a specially made outrigger system provides extra stability.

results.name: Air Jordan CP3.IX
results.story: Chris Paul’s signature CP3.IX debuted this Clippers-friendly colorway in 2015. Based in vibrant Soar blue, the mid-top’s Flight Web Fit System constructed upper is highlighted by navy and teal. Other signature details include Infrared branding, a teal outsole, and teal speckling throughout.

results.name: Air Jordan CP3.IX
results.story: Designed exclusively to highlight Chris Paul’s agility on the court, the Air Jordan CP3.IX features a composite mesh upper in black and Anthracite. The sneaker also sports foam overlays for support, a webbing lacing system for an adaptive fit, a nine-chamber Zoom unit for responsive cushioning, and a herringbone pattern on the outsole for traction.

results.name: Air Jordan CP3.IX
results.story: Designed to reflect Chris Paul’s agility on the court, the Air Jordan CP3.IX features a composite mesh upper dressed in black with foam overlays to ensure ultimate support. The sneaker also boasts black leather details, a padded blue mesh tongue for breathability, a webbing lace system for a lockdown fit, nine-chamber Zoom unit, and a herringbone pattern on the outsole for superior traction.

results.name: Jordan 4 Retro MCS 'Gym Red'
results.story: Inspired by the 1994 Air Jordan 4, these Air Jordan 4 MCS Cleats feature a Gym Red tumbled leather upper with a black mesh grate at the midfoot. Contrasting white emerges on the eyestay, Jumpman branding and heel patch as well as the midsole. Phylon foam provides cushioning, while a Power Channel plate sports 12 molded TPU cleats designed for both grass and turf.

results.name: Jordan Spizike GS 'Soar'
results.story: The ‘Soar’ color scheme of the Jordan Spiz’ike features Soar on the upper’s leather formation, while contrasting black accents emerge on the elephant print, tongue and sockliner. The hybrid lifestyle offering blends a series of design details from classic Jordan models, like the cement pattern and midsole from the 3, the wing flaps from the 4, the collar from the 5 and the tongue from the 6.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro PS 'Fuchsia Glow'
results.story: This preschool release presents a simple white and black colorway with Fuchsia Glow and Mulberry accents on the laces, outsole and branding. The white leather upper sports perforations on the side walls, while the multicolor sole houses a hidden Air unit. As the first shoe in the Jordan line to exclude Nike branding, it instead sports a Jumpman, ‘23’ and ‘Jordan’ to mark the look.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro TD 'Fuchsia Glow'
results.story: Toddlers can enjoy the cutting-edge designs of the Air Jordan 7 with this exclusive release. The Air Jordan 7 Retro TD 'Fuchsia Glow' features a white leather upper with perforations on the sides for breathability and matching paneling throughout. The sneaker also sports black details on the throat and ankle, Fuchsia Glow accents on the laces and Jumpman logo, and purple features on the heel tab and midsole plugs.

results.name: Jordan Super.Fly 4 'Fengshui'
results.story: The ‘Feng Shui’ edition of the Jordan Super.Fly 4 appears in the Charlotte Hornets’ team colors, featuring a combination of Bright Concord and Blue Lagoon tones throughout the upper’s mesh construction. The sneaker is finished with the Chinese characters for Feng Shui across the insoles, while a white outsole provides a clean finish.

results.name: Jordan Super.Fly 4
results.story: Jordan Brand drops Infrared tones onto the design of the Jordan Super.Fly 4, featuring a mostly Hyperfuse construction on the upper. Leather accents on the tongue and heel add a premium finish to the makeup, while white accents on the Jumpman branding and orange tones on the sockliner provide subtle contrast.

results.name: Air Jordan 14 Retro Low TD 'Laney' 2015
results.story: The Little Air Jordan 14 Low adapts elements of the sports car-inspired adult original for small feet. Issued in October 2015, this 'Laney' version's unofficial namesake is borrowed from Michael Jordan's high school alma mater due to its Varsity Royal nubuck shroud with Jumpman icons and metal eyelets. An elongated tongue and internal lacing give it a distinctive look. The foam midsole and rubber outsole provide cushioning and stability.

results.name: Jordan Westbrook 0
results.story: Unveiled on the feet of Russell Westbrook at New York Fashion Week in July 2015, this Cool Grey version of the Jordan Westbrook 0 is one of a handful of original colorways for the Oklahoma City point guard’s first signature sneaker. The lifestyle design reflects Russell’s appreciation for fashion and features layered premium leather with embossed details, webbed lacing, and a white vulcanized sole.

results.name: Jordan Westbrook 0
results.story: The Jordan Westbrook 0 applies a monochromatic finish to the upper of Russell Westbrook’s lifestyle silhouette. The shoe’s simple color scheme is enhanced with a suede upper and a subtle reptilian texture on the tonal leather mudguard. Metallic gold on the lace jewels—spelling out Russell Westbrook’s ‘Why Not?’ motto—offers contrasting pops of color. It all rests on a clean white rubber midsole.

results.name: Jordan Westbrook 0 'Military Green'
results.story: Russell Westbrook’s 0 silhouette with Jordan appears with chukka boot inspiration with fashion-forward details, like olive suede paneling, metal D-ring eyelets and a snakeskin embossed leather along the toe. Westbrook’s initials appear on the brass lace deubré, while the white vulcanized midsole adds a lifestyle appeal.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High 'Rare Air'
results.story: The ‘Rare Air’ version of the Air Jordan 1 Retro High appears with an elegant makeup that features a combination of black pebbled and smooth leather panels throughout the upper construction. Bronze accents appear on the contrasting details, like the branding, collar and outsole, while the Nike Air logo on the tongue is replaced with a Jumpman icon that’s applied with a Velcro patch. The Wings logo is replaced with AIR JORDAN on the side, this shoe was inspired by an early prototype sample seen in a photo shoot from Jordan’s rookie year.

results.name: Jordan Westbrook 0 'Black'
results.story: With this Jordan Westbrook 0 release from September 2015, Russell Westbrook’s first off-court silhouette takes on a sleek all-black color scheme. The mid-top features a premium leather upper, complemented by a reptilian-texture overlay and a partially translucent midsole. Exterior branding elements include an embossed Jumpman on the tongue and a metallic gold lace jewel.

results.name: Air Jordan 6 Retro Low GP 'Sport Fuchsia'
Air Jordan 1 Retro High BG 'Blue Lagoon'
Air Jordan 7 Retro PS 'Marvin the Martian'
results.story: The Air Jordan 7 Retro PS 'Marvin the Martian' features a black leather upper with perforations on the sidewall and ankle for breathability. The sneaker also sports University Red accents on the Jumpman logo, forefoot, and on the traction-forward sole unit. The colors are inspired by the popular cartoon character from Mars.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro BT 'Marvin The Martian'
Air Jordan 7 Retro TD Gift Pack 'Black Sport Fuchsia'
AJKO 'Chicago' 2015
results.story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG KO 2015 is a reissue of the original colorway in black, Varsity Red and white. Featuring an all-canvas build, the Jordan 1 KO is adorned with a Nike-branded tongue tag and a modified ‘Wings’ logo on the collar flap. The high-top is finished with white and red tooling borrowed from the Nike Vandal.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro Gift Pack TD 'Bordeaux' 2015
Air Jordan 7 Retro PS 'Bordeaux' 2015
results.story: One of the original colors of the Air Jordan 7, the ‘Bordeaux’ iteration of the AJ7 pre-school appears in a classic grey and black color scheme on the upper’s nubuck paneling. The geometric pattern on the tongue is complemented with Bordeaux accents on the heel and Jumpman branding.

results.name: Jordan Westbrook 0 'Black'
results.story: Created for off-court wear, the Jordan Westbrook 0 is finished with an all-black upper, featuring a full-grain leather construction with raised lines inspired by the Air Jordan 11. An embossed crocodile texture is featured near the midsole, while the contrasting white autoclave sole unit features a siped outsole for flexibility. Russell Westbrook’s personal ‘Why Not?’ motto is embossed on the shoe’s gold lace jewels.

results.name: Jordan Westbrook 0
results.story: Jordan Brand athlete Russell Westbrook gets his own signature lifestyle Jordan offering, featuring the Westbrook 0. Constructed with a premium white leather makeup on the upper, the sneaker features a mid-top design with a unique triangular eyelet system. Contrasted with a gold lace dubrae, the shoe also sits on a vulcanized midsole for a casual aesthetic.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro Gift Pack CB 'Hot Lava'
Jordan Westbrook 0
results.story: Russell Westbrook’s 0 silhouette with Jordan Brand is a lifestyle take on the brand’s long-standing basketball heritage. Featuring a chukka boot aesthetic that sports a vibrant Gym Red hue on the upper’s premium leather construction, the tongue implements a suede application, while the mudguard and toe are embossed with a faint crocodile print. The eyestay is equipped with triangular eyelets, while a vulcanized midsole is featured underfoot.

results.name: Jordan Jasmine GS
results.story: The Jordan Jasmine was inspired by Michael Jordan’s daughter, featuring a lifestyle-inspired high-top that’s formed with white tumbled leather. The mudguard is finished with a suede application, while gold Jordan and ‘Wings’ logos are displayed on the tongue and ankle. The shoe sits on a white vulcanized midsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Shattered Backboard' Sample
results.story: Inspired by Michael Jordan shattering a backboard during a Nike exhibition game in Italy in 1985, the ‘Shattered Backboard’ rendition of the Jordan 1 incorporates the black and orange color scheme from the uniform Jordan wore during the game. Sail accents on the quarter panel give the shoe a retro look, while the insole is stamped with a shattered backboard graphic.

results.name: Jordan Spizike BG
results.story: This retro release of the 2006 Jordan Spizike comes in boys sizing in a classic colorway including Jordan’s signature elephant print. The Spizike combines elements of several Jordan silhouettes that Mars Blackmon has advertised, including the Jordan 3, 4, 5, 6 and 20. The sneaker receives its name from film director Spike Lee, a long time ambassador of the Jordan Brand.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Chicago' 2015 Sample
Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Pinnacle' Sample
Jordan Son Of Mars Low 'Pro Stars'
Air Jordan 13 Retro PS 'Barons'
results.story: In 2014, Jordan Brand released an Air Jordan 1 Retro 'Barons' and an Air Jordan 9 'Barons,' both inspired by Jordan's time in baseball's minor leagues with Alabama’s Birmingham Barons. This Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Barons' dropped six months later. It was the first Air Jordan 13 to feature an iridescent patent leather mudguard. This infant-sized version also sports white quilted leather overlays and Wolf Grey tumbled leather at the toe.

results.name: Air Jordan Future Low 'Photo Blue'
results.story: Released in Spring 2015, the Jordan Future Low ‘Photo Blue’ sneaker makes a bright statement. The color is reminiscent of UNC’s team colors, where Michael Jordan played during college. This Jordan shoe is made with an allover mesh upper and features lightweight cushioning for a breathable feel with plush comfort. Asymmetrical laces realized in blue are offset by a lace panel trimmed with a black border. A contrasting white rubber sole reinforces the design.

results.name: Air Jordan 4 Retro BT 'Teal'
results.story: With classic elements, the Air Jordan 4 Retro BT packages the legendary history of the 1989 icon for first walkers. This 'Teal' kids' iteration—introduced in March 2015—applies an old-school color scheme on the leather upper, mesh inserts and quarter cage. Contrast laces provide lightweight containment, while a matching mudguard offers reinforcement. The bicolor midsole and multicolored rubber outsole mimic the look of the adult original.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro Gift Pack Infant 'Barcelona Nights'
Air Jordan 1 Retro Low 'Triple White'
results.story: The Air Jordan 1 has been termed ‘the sneaker that started it all,’ and this simple Triple White colorway can be viewed as something of a clean slate for the historic model. This low-top leather build is mostly true to the original high-top silhouette, with minor revisions in terms of branding: the OG ‘Wings’ logo is now embroidered on the heel, and a tonal Jumpman graces the lightly padded nylon tongue.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High BG 'Blake Griffin'
